 for bestpractices and # 404 Not Found

## Overview
Create a user-friendly 404 Not Found page for the Gbox360 Investor Perception Platform. The page serves as a polished, enterprise-grade error screen when routes are not found, while seamlessly offering navigation back to the dashboard or landing page. It should also surface the integrated Search & Filter experience (Typeahead company search and filters for NarrativeEvents and IPI timelines) as a quick path to discovery, enabling users to recover their context and continue exploration without friction. All components must be resilient to null/undefined data and follow runtime safety guidelines for arrays and API responses.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- A robust 404 Not Found page that gracefully handles missing routes, with clear messaging, helpful navigation, and quick access to core workflows (dashboard/landing). It should feel like a natural extension of the Gbox360 fintech UI, not a generic error screen.

Goals:
- Communicate that the requested route cannot be found in a calm, professional manner.
- Provide immediate, accessible options to navigate back to the dashboard or landing page.
- Introduce and integrate the Start of the Search & Filter experience to help users recover their place (typeahead company search and filters for NarrativeEvents and IPI timelines) so they can quickly continue meaningful exploration.
- Maintain visual consistency with the project’s visual language, typography, and spacing guidelines.
- Ensure accessibility (aria-labels, keyboard navigability, sufficient color contrast) and performance considerations.

UI elements and how they need to look:
- Prominent, friendly 404 headline (e.g., “We can’t find that page”) using a serif display font for the hero area.
- Subheading explaining the page isn’t available and offering options to navigate away.
- Primary actions:
  - Button: Go to Dashboard (green, primary)
  - Button: Go to Landing Page (outlined/secondary, teal/gray-teal accents)
- Central hero area with generous white space and a soft, editorial feel consistent with the hero styling in the project.
- A compact, inline Search & Filter module tailored for discovery:
  - Typeahead company search input
  - Filters for NarrativeEvents and IPI timelines (date range, event type, etc.)
  - Quick results listing to show potential match suggestions; ensure null safety for data
- Inline helper cards or tips that illustrate how to search or recover (optional but encouraged for UX richness).
- Visual guidance:
  - Clear hierarchy: large hero heading, medium subheading, then actions and search module
  - Cards with soft shadows and rounded corners
  - Subtle promotional floating card area (if used) with brown backdrop and a CTA in accent orange for “Learn more” or “Docs”

UI Style and Design System adherence:
- Align with the specified color palette and typography
- Maintain generous left/right padding, large hero heading, and 12-column grid implication with a max content width around 900–1000px for the hero
- Use rounded cards (16–20px) with subtle shadows (0 6px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.08))
- Interactive elements: green primary CTAs, teal/gray teal secondary actions, focus rings in the brand green
- Ensure hover and focus states provide a gentle lift or shadow intensification

API integrations:
- No external APIs are required for the 404 page itself, but the Search & Filter module will require integration with the existing backend that provides:
  - Company data (for typeahead)
  - NarrativeEvents and IPI timeline data (for filtering and drill-down)
- Since this is a 404 page, gracefully degrade to a static placeholder if APIs are unavailable, while still enabling navigation back to dashboard/landing.

Connected Features:
- Search & Filter: Typeahead company search and filters for NarrativeEvents and IPI timelines to help users quickly discover and drill down after landing on the 404 page.

Implementation Requirements

Frontend
- Pages/Routes:
  - 404 Not Found page route (e.g., /404 or wildcard catch-all) integrated into the app’s routing
- UI Components to Build:
  - ErrorHero
    - Large serif display heading
    - Subheading with friendly message
  - ActionBar
    - Primary Go to Dashboard button (green)
    - Secondary Go to Landing Page button (teal/gray-teal)
  - TypeaheadSearchModule
    - Input with autosuggest/typeahead behavior
    - Debounced fetch calls to fetch company suggestions (guard for nulls)
    - Show top suggestions with safe rendering: (data ?? []) and Array.isArray guards
  - FilterPanel (NarrativeEvents & IPI)
    - Date range picker (or simple from/to date inputs with validation)
    - Event type filter (multiselect or checkboxes)
    - Timeline filter (short presets)
    - Ensure default states are arrays/objects via useState([]) and useState({}) patterns
  - ResultsPreviewCard (optional)
    - Compact list of potential matches or recent items to guide user
    - All list rendering guarded with Array.isArray checks and data ?? []
  - FloatingPromotionalCard (optional)
    - Brown gradient/card with CTA in accent orange
- State Management and Safety:
  - useState initialization:
    - const [suggestions, setSuggestions] = useState<any[]>([])
    - const [filters, setFilters] = useState<{ [key: string]: any }>({})
  - Data handling:
    - When consuming API responses:
      - const items = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
      - Guard all map/filter/reduce with (items ?? []).map(...) or Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : []
  - Null/undefined guards:
    - Always use data ?? [] for arrays, and optional chaining for nested properties
- Accessibility:
  - ARIA labels for interactive elements
  - Keyboard navigable search and filters
  - High contrast text for headings and body
- Performance:
  - Debounce typeahead API calls
  - Lazy-load suggestions if hots paths are heavy
  - Cancel previous pending requests on new input

Backend
- APIs (if not yet present):
  - Company search/typeahead API endpoint: GET /api/companies/search?q={query}&limit=10
  - NarrativeEvents and IPI timeline filters: GET /api/ipi/timelines?companyId={id}&from={date}&to={date}&types={types}
- Database and functions:
  - Ensure endpoints return consistent shapes; if empty, return data: [] rather than null
  - Use idempotent reads; implement rate-limiting hints in docs
- Validation:
  - Validate query parameters, dates, and filters server-side
  - Return safe shapes: { data: Any[] } or { data: [] } if no results
  - Ensure no runtime crashes if data is absent

Integration
- Connect frontend components to backend endpoints with safe data handling:
  - Fetch typeahead suggestions with safeguards: const response = await fetch(...); const data = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
  - After selection, apply filters to NarrativeEvents and IPI timelines via timeline API
  - Pass results to UI components with safe defaults
- Routing and navigation:
  - Ensure 404 page is presented when route not found, but allow standard navigation to dashboard/landing
- State synchronization:
  - While on 404, maintain global UI state consistency (e.g., header nav highlights, user session)

User Experience Flow
- User lands on a non-existent URL
  - UI presents a friendly 404 message
  - Prominent primary action: Go to Dashboard
  - Secondary action: Go to Landing Page
  - A Typeahead Search module is visible to quickly find companies or docs
  - User types a company name:
    - Debounced API call fetches suggestions
    - Suggestions appear; user can click or navigate with keyboard
  - User may select a company and apply NarrativeEvents/IPI filters:
    - Date range and event-type filters refine data
    - The UI shows a compact results preview (if available)
  - User navigates away using actions or built-in navigation
- If API data is unavailable, the page gracefully falls back to static guidance with navigation options

Technical Specifications
- Data Models:
  - Company: { id: string, name: string, ticker?: string, ... }
  - NarrativeEvent: { id: string, source: string, speaker: string, role?: string, audienceClass?: string, rawText?: string, timestamp?: string, ... }
  - IPIEvent/Timeline: { id: string, companyId: string, date?: string, eventType?: string, narrativeId?: string, ... }
- API Endpoints:
  - GET /api/companies/search?q={query}&limit=10
  - GET /api/ipi/timelines?companyId={id}&from={date}&to={date}&types={types}
  - GET /api/ipi/current?companyId={id}
- Security:
  - User authentication context preserved; 404 page should enforce no sensitive data leakage
  - If endpoints require auth, attach tokens via standard authorization headers
- Validation:
  - Input validation for typeahead (sanitize, limit results)
  - Date range validation (from <= to, valid date formats)
  - Filters validation (allowed event types, valid IDs)

Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] The 404 page renders with a clear, brand-consistent hero, messages, and navigation actions
- [ ] Typeahead search loads suggestions safely; no runtime errors if API returns null or empty
- [ ] Filter panel correctly initializes with safe defaults (arrays/objects) and does not crash if API data is missing
- [ ] All array operations guarded: (items ?? []).map(...) or Array.isArray checks
- [ ] useState defaults for arrays/objects are correct: useState<Type[]>([]) and useState<{ [key: string]: any }>({})
- [ ] API responses are validated: const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
- [ ] Accessibility requirements met (aria labels, keyboard navigation)
- [ ] No sensitive data leaks; 404 does not expose internal routing details
- [ ] Styles align with the Visual Style guidelines (colors, typography, spacing) and overall design system

UI/UX Guidelines
